{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"safe","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","text":"Index"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Element","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa"},{"text":"? { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]}],"name":"index"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returning ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"range simply result in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example usage:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, ","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection\/subscript(safe:)"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Accesses the element at the specified position in a safe manner."}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftExtras","relatedModules":["Swift"]}],"fragments":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"